# Remote access to WinCC Unified PC Runtime & HMI Unified Panels

  * Entry

  * Associated product(s)




How do I set up remote access to SIMATIC WinCC Unified PC Runtime, SIMATIC HMI Unified Comfort Panels, SIMATIC HMI Unified Basic Panels?

[Web Access (Remote)](https://support.industry.siemens.com/cs/#chapter_5634777_0)[ \- Unified PC Runtime](https://support.industry.siemens.com/cs/#chapter_5634777_1)[ \- Unified Panel (Basic/Comfort)](https://support.industry.siemens.com/cs/#chapter_5634777_2)[Network access](https://support.industry.siemens.com/cs/#chapter_5634777_3)[](https://support.industry.siemens.com/cs/#chapter_5634777_4)[ \- Unified PC Runtime](https://support.industry.siemens.com/cs/#chapter_5634777_5)[ \- Unified Panel (Basic/Comfort)](https://support.industry.siemens.com/cs/#chapter_5634777_6)[](https://support.industry.siemens.com/cs/#chapter_5634777_7)[Other access types](https://support.industry.siemens.com/cs/#chapter_5634777_8)[ \- Mobile Devices](https://support.industry.siemens.com/cs/#chapter_5634777_9)[ \- HMI connection with CPU](https://support.industry.siemens.com/cs/#chapter_5634777_10)[ \- Central user administration with UMC](https://support.industry.siemens.com/cs/#chapter_5634777_11)

## Web Access (Remote)

A WinCC Unified PC Runtime is accessed via a web browser, see:[Which browser can I use for SIMATIC WinCC Unified PC Runtime?](https://support.industry.siemens.com/cs/document/109757952/which-browser-can-i-use-for-simatic-wincc-unified-pc-runtime-?lc=en-in).  
Depending on the end device and the Unified application, there are different requirements for access and [Settings for communication with WinCC Unified Runtime on the runtime device](https://support.industry.siemens.com/cs/document/109806850/settings-for-communication-with-wincc-unified-pc-runtime?lc=en-in).The different connection options between WinCC Unified PC Runtime and the HMI Unified Panels are described below.

  


##  \- Unified PC Runtime

> **Web Browser Access**
> 
> Prerequisites and steps are documented in: [HMI WinCC Unified V20 - Display runtime](https://docs.tia.siemens.cloud/r/en-us/v20/operating-unified-pc-rt-unified/starting-and-displaying-runtime-rt-unified/displaying-runtime-rt-unified).  
> Der Zugriff über Webbrowser (z. B. Chrome, Edge) via: https://[IP-Adresse oder Hostname]:[Port]/WebRH  
> Configure communication settings via [Settings for communication with WinCC Unified Runtime on the runtime device](https://support.industry.siemens.com/cs/document/109806850/settings-for-communication-with-wincc-unified-pc-runtime?lc=en-in).

>   
> 

##  \- Unified Panel (Basic/Comfort)

> **Web Browser Access (Integrated Web Server)  
> ** As an alternative to direct operation of the runtime project on the Unified Comfort Panel, there is the option of accessing the runtime project of the operating device via a web browser. The requirements and procedure can be found in the corresponding manual:

>   * [HMI Unified Basic Panels - Web Access to the HMI device](https://docs.tia.siemens.cloud/r/unified_basic_panels_enus_20/operating-the-control-panel/runtime-properties/web-client).
>   * [HMI Unified Comfort Panels - Web Access to the HMI device](https://docs.tia.siemens.cloud/r/unified_comfort_panels_enus_20/operating-the-control-panel/runtime-properties/web-client).  
>   
> 
> 

> 
> In order for the web browser to establish a secure connection to the runtime of the HMI Unified Comfort Panel, the certificate must be known to be trustworthy in the web browser. Information on the procedure and installation of the certificate is described in the article
> 
> [Installing a certificate in the browser when accessing via web client (UCP)](https://docs.tia.siemens.cloud/r/en-us/v20/using-distributed-systems-rt-unified/web-client-rt-unified/installing-a-certificate-in-the-browser-when-accessing-via-web-client-ucp-rt-unified).  
> 

> **Sm@rtServer (Limited Support)  
> **  
> **Unified Comfort Panel**  
>  The Unified Comfort Panels enable secure and synchronized remote access via the integrated Sm@rtServer.  
> To establish a remote desktop connection to an HMI Unified Comfort Panel, the Sm@rtServer must be activated on the panel. As soon as the Sm@rtServer is started on an operating device, you can access the HMI Unified Comfort Panel either via the client application or a VNC client. The connections are set up via the TCP/IP protocol with password protection.  
> Information can be found in the manual: [HMI Unified Comfort Panels - Remote Connection](https://docs.tia.siemens.cloud/r/unified_comfort_panels_enus_20/operating-the-control-panel/network-and-internet/remote-connection). 

>   
> 

> **Unified Basic Panel (****Limited Support****)  
> ** Unified Basic Panels can only be used as Client and "OPC UA Clients", but not as Sm@rtServers or OPC UA Servers. An overview of the restrictions can be found here: [HMI Unified Basic Panel - Unsupported functions](https://docs.tia.siemens.cloud/r/en-us/v20/wincc-unified-rt-unified/performance-features-rt-unified/general-technical-data-rt-unified/unsupported-functions-rt-unified)

>   
> 

## Network access

## 

##  \- Unified PC Runtime

> To access WinCC Unified PC Runtime from an external network, proceed as described in the following entry:  
> [Configuring access to WinCC Unified PC Runtime from an external network](https://support.industry.siemens.com/cs/document/109804116/configuring-access-to-wincc-unified-pc-runtime-from-an-external-network-?lc=en-in).  
>   
> 

##  \- Unified Panel (Basic/Comfort)

## 

> You can connect a Network Drive to the Unified Panel for a file transfer. This function is available from a certain version in the following Unified Panels:
> 
>   * Unified Comfort Panel from Image V17 Upd 4.
>   * Unified Basic Panel from Image V19 Upd 2.
> 

> 
> Further information for Unified Comfort Panels can be found in the[Manual: Unified Comfort Panel - Network Drive](https://docs.tia.siemens.cloud/r/unified_comfort_panels_enus_20/operating-the-control-panel/network-and-internet/network-drive).  
> For Unified Basic Panels, please refer to the Readme file in the article: [Image Downloads for SIMATIC HMI Operator Panels: Unified Basic Panels](https://support.industry.siemens.com/cs/document/109825897/image-downloads-for-simatic-hmi-operator-panels-unified-basic-panels?lc=en-in). 

>   
> 

## Other access types

##  \- Mobile Devices

> When accessing WinCC Unified PC Runtime from mobile devices (smartphones, tablets, etc.), there are some special features to consider. For example, there are different procedures for installing certificates in the web browser.  
> Further information can be found in the entry: [Encrypted access from end devices to a WinCC Unified Runtime](https://support.industry.siemens.com/cs/document/109777591/access-of-mobile-devices-to-wincc-unified-pc-runtime?lc=en-in).  
>   
> 

##  \- HMI connection with CPU

> When accessing a CPU from a WinCC Unified PC Runtime or an HMI Unified Panel, there are some special features depending on the firmware. Below you will find further information on the corresponding contributions depending on the connection setup:
> 
>   * [Verbindungsaufbau zwischen WinCC Unified und CPU mit Firmware 2.9/4.5](https://support.industry.siemens.com/cs/document/109961590/establishing-a-connection-between-wincc-unified-and-cpu-with-firmware-2.9-4.5?lc=en-in) .
>   * [Configuration of an HMI connection to S7-1500/S7-1200 CPUs](https://support.industry.siemens.com/cs/document/109955142/configuration-of-an-hmi-connection-to-s7-1500-s7-1200-cpus?lc=en-in).  
> 
> 


> **Connection with a simulated CPU  
> ** Information on configuring a connection between a simulated CPU and WinCC Unified PC Runtime can be found in the following article: [Establish connection between simulated CPU S7-1500 (S7-PLCSIM Advanced) and WinCC Unified PC Runtime](https://support.industry.siemens.com/cs/document/109793854/establish-connection-between-simulated-cpu-s7-1500-\(s7-plcsim-advanced\)-and-wincc-unified-pc-runtime?lc=en-in). 
> 
>   
> 

##  \- Central user administration with UMC

> **Unified Runtime**

> User Management Component (UMC) allows you to set up a central user administration. User management with the "User Management Component (UMC)" allows you to set up a central user administration. Further information can be found here:
> 
>   * [Central User Management with "User Management Component (UMC)"](https://support.industry.siemens.com/cs/document/109780337/central-user-management-with-user-management-component-\(umc\)-?lc=en-in).
>   * [WinCC Unified V20 - Central user management and UMC](https://docs.tia.siemens.cloud/r/en-us/v20/configuring-users-and-roles-rt-unified/basics-rt-unified/central-user-management-rt-unified). 
> 

> 
>   
> 
> 
> **Unified Panel (Basic/Comfort)**
> 
>   
> 
> 
> The local or central user administration is configured in TIA Portal and transferred to the HMI Unified Panel during loading.   
> You can view the current settings on the Unified Panel under "Settings" -> "Security" -> "UMAC Settings". It is not possible to switch between local and central user administration, as the configuration of the local or central user administration takes place during project planning and this configuration is then transferred or loaded to the Unified Panel.
> 
>   
> 
> 
> The "UMAC Settings" (User Management and Access Control) indicate whether the Unified Panel works with local or central user administration.
> 
> Further information can be found in the [HMI Unified Comfort Panels - UMAC Settings](https://docs.tia.siemens.cloud/r/unified_comfort_panels_enus_20/operating-the-control-panel/security/umac-settings), [HMI Unified Basic Panels - UMAC Settings](https://docs.tia.siemens.cloud/r/unified_basic_panels_enus_20/operating-the-control-panel/security/umac-settings).

  
  


